When I worked for Dar es Salaam's Daily News in the early 70s, we often "stole"stories from Western news agencies. The ideological debates that the 1967 Azimio la Arusha unleashed had awakened in us deep suspicion over the agencies’ sermons on “fairness” and “independence”.
It had struck us that they themselves knowingly peddled as truths certain lies supplied by their governments portraying those governments as angels in international crisis spots and their enemies as the very Antichrist.  



